super::metadata::{SessionMetadata, SessionStatus};\nuse super::repository::{SessionFilter, SessionRepository};\nuse crate::os::Os;\n\n/// Filesystem-based session repository\npub struct FileSystemRepository {\n    os: Os,\n}\n\nimpl FileSystemRepository {\n    pub fn new(os: Os) -> Self {\n        Self { os }\n    }\n\n    fn sessions_dir(&self) -> Result<PathBuf, SessionError> {\n        Ok(self.os.env.current_dir()?.join(\".amazonq/sessions\"))\n    }\n}\n\n#[async_trait]\nimpl SessionRepository for FileSystemRepository {\n    async fn get(&self, id: &str) -> Result<SessionMetadata, SessionError> {\n        let session_dir = self.sessions_dir()?.join(id);\n        load_metadata(&session_dir).await\n    }\n\n    async fn save(&self, metadata: &SessionMetadata) -> Result<(), SessionError> {\n        let session_dir = self.sessions_dir()?.join(&metadata.id);\n        save_metadata(&session_dir, metadata).await\n    }\n\n    async fn delete(&self, id: &str) -> Result<(), SessionError> {\n        let session_dir = self.sessions_dir()?.join(id);\n        tokio::fs::remove_dir_all(session_dir).await?;\n        Ok(())\n    }\n\n    async fn list(&self, filter: SessionFilter) -> Result<Vec<SessionMetadata>, SessionError> {\n        let sessions_dir = self.sessions_dir()?;\n\n        if !sessions_dir.exists() {\n            return Ok(Vec::new());\n        }\n\n        let mut sessions = Vec::new();\n        let mut entries = tokio::fs::read_dir(&sessions_dir).await?;\n\n        while let Some(entry) = entries.next_entry().await? {\n            if entry.file_type().await?.is_dir() {\n                if let Ok(metadata) = load_metadata(&entry.path()).await {\n                    sessions.push(metadata);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Apply status filter\n        if let Some(status) = filter.status {\n            sessions.retain(|s| s.status == status);\n        }\n\n        // Apply search filter\n        if let Some(search) = filter.search {\n            let search_lower = search.to_lowercase();\n            sessions.retain(|s| {\n                s.first_message.to_lowercase().contains(&search_lower)\n                    || s.name\n                        .as_ref()\n                        .map_or(false, |n| n.to_lowercase().contains(&search_lower))\n            });\n        }\n\n        // Sort by last_active, most recent first\n        sessions.sort_by(|a, b| b.last_active.cmp(&a.last_active));\n\n        // Apply limit\n        if let Some(limit) = filter.limit {\n            sessions.truncate(limit);\n        }\n\n        Ok(sessions)\n    }\n\n    async fn exists(&self, id: &str) -> Result<bool, SessionError> {\n        let session_dir = self.sessions_dir()?.join(id);\n        Ok(session_dir.exists())\n    }\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n    use tempfile::TempDir;\n\n    fn create_test_os(temp_dir: &TempDir) -> Os {\n        Os::test_with_root(temp_dir.path())\n    }\n\n    #[tokio::test]\n    async fn test_save_and_get() {\n        let temp_dir = TempDir::new().unwrap();\n        let os = create_test_os(&temp_dir);\n        let repo = FileSystemRepository::new(os);\n\n        let metadata = SessionMetadata::new(\"test-1\", \"Test session\");\n        repo.save(&metadata).await.unwrap();\n\n        let loaded = repo.get(\"test-1\").await.unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(loaded.id, \"test-1\");\n        assert_eq!(loaded.first_message, \"Test session\");\n    }\n\n    #[tokio::test]\n    async fn test_list_with_filter() {\n        let temp_dir = TempDir::new().unwrap();\n        let os = create_test_os(&temp_dir);\n        let repo = FileSystemRepository::new(os);\n\n        let meta1 = SessionMetadata::new(\"id-1\", \"Active session\");\n        repo.save(&meta1).await.unwrap();\n\n        let mut meta2 = SessionMetadata::new(\"id-2\", \"Archived session\");\n        meta2.archive();\n        repo.save(&meta2).await.unwrap();\n\n        let filter = SessionFilter {\n            status: Some(SessionStatus::Active),\n            ..Default::default()\n        };\n        let results = repo.list(filter).await.unwrap();\n\n        assert_eq!(results.len(), 1);\n                 "new_str": "    /// List all sessions\n    #[instrument(skip(self), fields(session_count))]\n    pub async fn list_sessions(&self) -> Result<Vec<SessionMetadata>, SessionError> {\n        let start = std::time::Instant::now();\n        debug!(\"Listing sessions\");\n\n        let filter = SessionFilter::default();\n        let sessions = self.repository.list(filter).await?;\n\n        let duration_ms = start.elapsed().as_millis() as u64;\n        self.metrics.record_list(duration_ms, sessions.len());\n        info!(count = sessions.len(), duration_ms, \"Listed sessions successfully\");\n        tracing::Span::current().record(\"session_count\", sessions.len());\n\n        Ok(sessions)\n    }",
                "old_str": "    /// List all sessions from the repository\n    #[instrument(skip(self), fields(session_count))]\n    pub async fn list_sessions(&self) -> Result<Vec<SessionMetadata>, SessionError> {\n        let start = std::time::Instant::now();\n        debug!(\"Listing sessions from repository\");\n        \n        let mut sessions = self.repository.list(&Default::default()).await?;\n\n        // Sort by last_active, most recent first\n        sessions.sort_by(|a, b| b.last_active.cmp(&a.last_active));\n\n        let duration_ms = start.elapsed().as_millis() as u64;\n        self.metrics.record_list(duration_ms, sessions.len());\n        info!(count = sessions.len(), duration_ms, \"Listed sessions successfully\");\n        tracing::Span::current().record(\"session_count\", sessions.len());\n\n        Ok(sessions)\n    }",

    "Perfect! Now I have the complete picture. Let me provide the answer:\n\n## Answer: `/compact` Uses the **Main LLM Model**\n\nThe `/compact` command sends a summarization request to the **same main LLM model** you're using for the conversation (e.g., Claude, GPT-4, etc.), **not** a local model.\n\n### How it works:\n\n1. **Creates a special prompt** asking the model to summarize the conversation history in a structured format (bullet points, third person, no conversational fluff)\n\n2. **Sends to main API**: Calls `client.send_message()`  `generate_assistant_response()` which goes to the CodeWhisperer streaming API (the same backend as regular chat messages)\n\n3. **Uses current model**: The request includes `self.model_info.as_ref().map(|m| m.model_id.clone())` - meaning it uses whatever model you have selected (via `/model` command or default)\n\n4. **Replaces history**: Once the summary is generated, it replaces the conversation history with the summary to free up context space\n\n### Key code evidence:\n\n```rust\n// From conversation.rs line 777\nuser_input_message: summary_message\n    .into_user_input_message(\n        self.model_info.as_ref().map(|m| m.model_id.clone()), // Uses current model\n        &tools\n    ),\n```\n\n```rust\n// From api_client/mod.rs line 378\npub async fn send_message(&self, conversation: ConversationState) -> ... {\n    // ... sends to CodeWhisperer streaming API\n    client.generate_assistant_response()\n        .conversation_state(conversation_state)\n        .send()\n        .await\n}\n```\n\n**There is no local model involved** - it's a regular API call to the backend with a special system prompt that instructs the LLM to create a summary document rather than respond conversationally.\n[Tool uses: none]",

    "## Why `/compact` Does a Bad Job\n\nBased on the code, here are the likely issues:\n\n### 1. **It's sent as a USER message, not a SYSTEM message**\n```rust\nUserMessage::new_prompt(summary_content.clone(), None)\n```\nThe summarization instructions are sent as if the **user** is asking for a summary, not as system-level instructions.
